or_ratio, server_error_ratio.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Error ratios rose from 0.0 to 0.67 (frontend-1), alongside `rrt_max` increases.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"redis-cart-0\",\n      \"reason\": \"Server error spikes indicate potential backend data store instability or throughput issues. Metrics: error_ratio, server_error_ratio.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"P99 of error_ratio and server_error_ratio increased to 1.22 from 0.0.\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"checkoutservice\",\n      \"reason\": \"Increased response time max and average indicate checkout service delay. Metrics: rrt_max, rrt.\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max changed significantly, affecting checkout processing performance.\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n### Analysis Summary:\nThe anomalies primarily stem from service-level issues rather than node-specific problems. The significant increase in error ratios and response times across `frontend`, `redis`, and `checkoutservice` imply potential service misconfigurations or overload situations. These should be investigated further for root-cause resolution in application configurations or resource allocations."}
